        "description": " ORDER ADOPTING REPORT AND RECOMMENDATIONS - Consistent with the recommendation by the Magistrate Judge, Plaintiff's 42 U.S.C. § 1983 claims against Defendants for retaliation in violation of the First Amendment and deprivations of due proce ss in violation of the Fourteenth Amendment is DISMISSED with prejudice for failure to state a claim upon which relief can be granted, pursuant to 28 U.S.C. §§ 1915(e)(2)(B) and 1915A(b)(1); Plaintiff's state-law claim against Defendan ts for fraud is DISMISSED with prejudice for failure to state a claim upon which relief can be granted, pursuant to 28 U.S.C. §§ 1915(e)(2)(B) and 1915A(b)(1); The Court certifies that pursuant to 28 U.S.C. § 1915(a)(3) that an appeal  of this Order would not be taken in good faith; and this dismissal shall count as a \"strike\" in accordance with the Prison Litigation Reform Act of 1995.   Signed by Judge Michael R. Barrett on 11/19/2025. (kkz)(This document has been sent by regular mail to the party(ies) listed in the NEF that did not receive electronic notification.)",
